The paper discusses improvements and variations for LSTM networks in the context of natural language processing, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of Monte Carlo test-time model averaging and deep vector averaging suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. The use of residual connections is a common technique in neural networks, which suggests a focus on neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper also mentions text classification datasets, which suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) techniques for processing text data.
